<br>
Thanks again, and sorry for the grammer mistakes         <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umordier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mordier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/6/01 8:03:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice 4 worst rogue on RZ, kinda long</span><hr size=1> Hmm, where to begin heh.<br>
<br>
First of all, the rogue's biggest advantage is surprise.  If you get the jump on someone you've got a great chance of victory.  If you get jumped, it's a heck of alot tougher to win.  You need to think like a rogue; hunt.  Hunt your prey.  There were times where I shadowed someone for over 20 minutes waiting for the perfect moment to strike, and b/c I didn't see the right situation I let them go.  It's the thrill of the hunt that is most exciting.  You sound like you've mainly been the hunted.  Become the hunter.<br>
<br>
Have confidence in yourself.  If you enter a fight being afraid that you're going to lose, you'll lose.  If you enter a fight thinking about what you're going to bag first, you'll lose.  Sounds cheesy, but it's true.<br>
<br>
Poison.  Learn it and live by it.  There are great poison guides here on the Safehouse.  Use them to learn the skill and then apply it to your battles.  It'll take a little while to get the hang of it, and you'll waste some time gathering components, but without it you'll always be a poor-man's rogue.<br>
<br>
Ok, to answer your specific questions:<br>
<br>
1)no drop items.  Well I only had two I think.  The burning rapier and the mask of deception.  The rapier is a great weapon, read up on the quest.  <br>
<br>
2)Mask of Deception.  This will be simple for you to get if you're a dark elf.  Just get a map of Guk (upper and lower) and sneak down there.  If there's a group at the spawn site just tell them you'd like to loot a mask.  It should be easy really, aside from the obvious mob danger.<br>
<br>
3)Poisons.  Root and snare are the two best, blind is also nice when used in the right place (it's great indoors).  The cheapest ones that are still valuable are the dot poison and weaken poison.  Weaken, if used on the right opponent is a great way to snare someone (their str goes down and they become encumbered).<br>
<br>
4)Guilds.  Dunno, I played on Vallon Zek<br>
<br>
5)If you make an alt, don't make a rogue.  Stick with what you have.<br>
<br>
  You'll hurt a little b/c you didn't put any points into strength, which is arguably the most important rogue stat, but it won't be a big deal.  Boost your str a bit with items and you'll be fine.  Get it up over 100.  Don't think about starting over, just use what you have to your advantage.  <br>
<br>
  That's it for now, hope it helps some.  Realize that alot of the people you're fighting have been playing this game for a long time.  Simple experience makes a big difference, so you'll just get better the more you play.<br>
