<br>
Thanks to all those who posted   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=legit>Legit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/9/01 9:50:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice 4 worst rogue on RZ, kinda long</span><hr size=1> Well, from someone who has played on RZ since day 1 and continues to only play on RZ I'll try and answer some of your questions that are more server-specific.<br>
<br>
I would advise getting Magic Resist gear ASAP, as a high MR will help you live longer (or get away easier) than any other resist. Items to look for: gold wolf's eye bracers (+7x2), silver wolf's eye necklace (+4, platinum is too expensive to risk at your lvl), bloodstained mantle (+3 str, +10 MR), dwarven ringmail tunic (+7 or 8 MR/FR/CR), runed bone fork (+10 MR/FR/CR) = total MR +46 with your base of 25 = 71 MR. Granted with 60pp in the bank you could probably only get the necklace and bs mantle for now, but these are easy enough to save up for. Don't worry about losing these items either as it is easy enough to set up a hotkey bank to quickly bag them if necessary.<br>
<br>
As far as guilds on RZ are concerned, there are many PK, anti-PK, and neutral guilds to be found. Invitations into many of them are not too hard to get and undoubtedly a guild to hunt with will provide you some protection from gankers. If you're worried about your reputation then don't join a self-proclaimed PK guild, and if you'd rather avoid most confrontations then look for a more neutral guild as anti-PK guilds tend to fight as much if not more than some PK guilds. Honestly though, having had characters in all 3 types, very few will truly remember you unless you are a &quot;hardcore&quot; PKer and go on daily killing sprees for several weeks. Everyone on RZ has killed other PCs from time to time whether in self-defense or just for kicks, and no one expects you to have a perfect reputation just to be viable in the 50+ game. Just as long as people get along with you, you should have no problems.<br>
<br>
As was stated earlier, get some experience on the attacking side of PvP. You'd be surprised how many people will run from you after a nice backstab followed by a flurry of hits that they weren't expecting. Look mainly for INT casters as targets early on, avoid melees til you get used to strafing and jousting unless you have a few blind poisons ready. Casters are easy to interrupt if you just keep beating on them, plus not all casters will spin fast enough to keep you from getting backstabs in, so you should have no trouble winning.<br>
<br>
