<br>
All on Rallos Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulivonya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Livonya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/10/01 2:08:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.uweb.ucsb.edu/~rgratzer/images/circle2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice 4 worst rogue on RZ, kinda long</span><hr size=1> I play a rogue on Rallos (52 right now), so here's my advice: for weapons in pvp at your level I would go for ones that are as fast as possible. I suppose this is sorta pretty obvious, but I have seen lower rogues kick ass with the right weapons. As for armor, first off since you can make your own banded for cheap, I would suggest wearing it and not bagging it when fighting. AC can play a big part in not getting creamed by pets and other melees. You also won't have to spend your time bagging and can focus on the killing. But you may not want to take this advice since you might be getting killed a real lot and would have to be replacing the lost banded all the time. I just feel more confident when I have gear on when killing people, and unless you feel banded is too precious to lose, it can be a real benefit to not care about bagging.<br>
<br>
I won't try to give anymore advice because it probably won't help. I practically never pvp'ed at lower levels, so I don't have any hands on experience to tell about (I was past level 30 within the first 3 months of Rallos and the server was a little tamer back then).<br>
